column4: Department of Sociology, Delhi School of Economics
column58:
DU administration is very poor. I am really sorry for such a feedback but its necessary.
1. During admission no mail was sent to the successful candidates and just a notice was displayed on the website.
2. The same problem goes with every essential notices related to academics, scholarships, seminars and so on. If the idea is to put notices on the boards and just put it on the university website then what is the use of all the IT infrastructure. 
3. Even during pandemic everything had to be dome by going to the department. What is the need of technology if for every small thing I have to go to from my department then to BRS office, scholarship department, finance department. 
4. There is no proper chain of information. We were not even told which document to furnish at the time of admission. What are the forms needed to be filled and documents needed to be signed. At least university and departments should provide clear written guidelines. 
5.  Even though remote access to library is provided but it takes weeks to get an enrollment number for a PhD candidate. I do not understand why University cannot automatically generate it and sent to us. I even did not knew about it. At least provide clear guidelines on how to get digital access to various national and international journals. 
6. Why cannot university provide access to plagiarism tools like Urkund and Turnitin to students. How easy it would be for students to get plagiarism tests and rework on the research.
7. Please provide a mechanism so that departments at least send us mails regarding academics, scholarships, seminars etc. Most of the time in case a person forget to look into the website he/she might loose on scholarships.
8. I will not comment on offline mode of studies as I was not fortunate enough to witness that. 
9. Further, please provide a centralized system for information on hostels. There are scattered and its difficult to go each hostel to get forms and check availability. To get admission in one is a tiring process. Please make it smooth. Please make it centralize.

1) At one point of time there is a lot of activities going in various departments in a college/campus. Every college/campus can put up a broad plan (for the year) of those activities up on a web portal. It would become easier for a student to know and plan in advance where he/she would like to participate. The winners from various forums could also be put up on the portal and the activities should be monitored in real time. It would bring in a feeling of competition and transparency. A new comer would largely benefit. A more interactive alumnus would evolve. 
2) Similar transparency can be brought about in the allocation of funds for various fests. Fests are a learning curve for a student. Less participative students would also benefit and learn how to manage the resources when a proper allocation to various activities is laid out at one place. Departments would learn from each other. 
3) College elections can be better organised when one on one debate take place between candidates. A more informed voter would have more reasons to elect a candidate. Candidates will have to work hard on their skills and money's strength would decrease. 
4) Quality of grounds can improve. A more participative audience with better seating facilities will motivate players to do better.

I have put very honest thoughts while filling this survey. it answers all my experience.

The reduced academic calendar this year is quite troublesome. Internships and extra curricular activities play a crucial role in todays life. The 2 months summer break the the students receive helps to explore new things, understand themselves better and go out and try different stuffs one would not find the time to do when the classes run in full throttle. 
In regards to this the decision by the University both this and the previous years to restrict the Summer break to just a week is something I found  not aligned to the needs of the current generation. At times when other university students do their Upskilling in these two months, DU students have to take a seat back and lose on some great opportunities. This reduces their acceptability as students with high intellect and creativeness.

Administration services need to get MUCH better in the university. Every little thing requires too much hassle and the admin staff is hardly helpful or kind.
Evaluation of exam papers need serious improvement. Really messes up marks despite brilliant performance. It's a major issue as it's a question of one's future opportunities.

Department syllabi needs to be updated and learning needs to be a little less focused on theory. 
The pedagogy and the evaluation system within the tutorial programme in the department of sociology needs serious changes. So many batchmates have had horrible experiences with no solution from the department.

The semesters are too short and hence a lot of academic pressure piles up on a student. The session breaks are also absent preventing students to work in internships, educational workshops and the like. A very hectic academic life often leads to mental fatigue and exasperation. If this could be improved, it would be highly helpful. 

Also, please urgently begin â€œresidentsâ€admission to the hostels. Up till now the hostels were only admitting students on a guest basis.
Keep improving. There is much scope. Never forget the centrality of student's interests as central to academic policies.

The process of learning to be more effective

1. Only one student ID card should be made, which should include bus pass, library card, health card, and sports card (assent and fee should be taken from the student only at the time of admission).
2. The number of hostels should be more in the university and colleges, and the university should start thinking towards becoming a fully residential university as mentioned in the University of Delhi Act 1922.
3. There is an urgent need for up-gradation in the basic facilities like Sitting Hall, Table Chair, Books, AC, Drinking Water and Bathroom in the Central Arts Library and other departmental libraries also.
4. There is a need to improve the food standards of various canteens in the university and colleges. There is a need to create a monitoring body for all hostels, university, colleges messes and canteens.
5. There is a need to create a complaint box on the university website where students can raise their complaints by keeping their privacy safe.
6. If the first suggestion is not met, then a single University ID number should be provided to each student, which can be used in place of the signature of the HOD or Principal for making Library Card, Hostel Admission, GYM Card, Health Card, etc.
7. Market-oriented courses should be started in the university and the colleges.
8. Through the courses, attention should be paid to the holistic development of the student.
9. Accountability should be fixed for administrative work and most of the administrative facilities should be provided through the university website (online mode).

Most subjects are taught in such an uninteresting manner that only 10% to 20% is retained after classroom. Tests and assignments take up 90% of students' time and majority of the remaining 10% goes in going to college, attending classes and coming back home. I urge the university to take a balanced approach which facilitates learning keeping in mind the mental and physical health of the students.
